sql:
SELECT name
FROM researchers
WHERE last_login = (SELECT MAX(last_login) FROM researchers);

external_knowledge:
- 'unlocked the treasure of chlorophyll knowledge' refers to accessing samples with high chlorophyll a concentration; 
- 'season' refers to a period of 3 months; 
- 'most' refers to having the highest average chlorophyll a concentration of the accessed samples among the top 3 researchers with the highest access counts.

sql:
SELECT name
FROM researchers
WHERE researcher_id IN (SELECT researcher_id FROM reporting);

SELECT site_name
FROM sites
WHERE last_updated = (SELECT MAX(last_updated) FROM sites);

external_knowledge:
- The researcher ID '1' can refer to a specific researcher's ID number; 
- Average chlorophyll a value represents an aggregated average calculated across a specified range of chlorophyll a concentration values; 
- Maximum access count denotes the highest number of access events recorded at each site; 
- 'Sites sampled by researcher 1' means the research sites for which researcher 1 has submitted samples.
